# Stop conditions

Stop and report instead of continuing when:

- No source issue
- No file-touch allowlist
- Unclear scope
- Authority conflict with canonical docs
- Unverified PR or live gate state for readiness claims
- Mixed intent in one PR
- Edits outside the approved allowlist
- GitHub primary rate limit, secondary rate limit, abuse throttling, or suspected unauthenticated GitHub API access

## Boundaries

- Do not expand scope; record discovered work in the source issue
- Do not merge pull requests unless explicitly authorized
- Do not close or relabel GitHub issues unless explicitly authorized
- When cloud workflow instructs branch creation, use `cursor/<descriptive-name>-2e48`

Full stop conditions and execution law live in `docs/ops/ai/CORE-RULES.md` and `docs/ops/ai/SHARED-AGENT-RULES.md`.
